metadata.title: Polish Trail catches of walleye Pollock chalcogramma in the international waters of the Bering Sea in the Summer of 1993.  Bull. Sea Fish. Inst. Gdynia 1996 No. 2 (138) 29 - 37
metadata.description: Distribution and CPUE of Pollock and length and age of adult Pollock were presented.  Longer concentrations of juvenile Pollock was located.  Age of juveniles indicated that spawning took place between March 17 through April 7, 1993
metadata.notes:
Purpose: To determine the geophysical disturbance of Pollock in donut hole.
